# Lab: Day 1 — Linux Core Setup, SSH & Static IP

## Lab Metadata
- Phase: 1 – Core Systems
- Disciplines: Linux Systems, Networking, DevOps Foundation
- Roles Enabled: Linux SysAdmin, Junior DevOps Engineer, DevOps Engineer
- Duration: 2–3 hours
- Lab Version: 1.1

## Lab Overview
Provision a Linux VM with a **static IP**, secure SSH, firewall, and baseline packages. Foundation for hybrid and cloud-ready architectures.

## Step-by-Step Execution
1. VM Creation — provision baseline Linux VM for labs
2. SSH Setup — enable secure passwordless access
3. Update OS & Install Packages — ensure latest patches and essential tools
4. Hostname & Hosts Configuration — consistent name resolution
5. Static IP Verification — confirm predictable networking
6. Firewall Configuration — basic network security
7. Time Sync — ensure accurate logs and monitoring
8. Connectivity Verification — confirm network & SSH

## Automation / Configs
- VM_Setup.sh
- SSH_Config.md
- Hosts_Config.md

## Failure Injection
- SSH key misconfiguration
- Firewall blocks access
- Static IP conflicts

